channel.title: INfinance
channel.description: This is a randomly ordered feed of the most recent entries from INfinance, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Google’s antitrust woes spark analyst downgrade of Alphabet’s stock
item.description: JMP Securities cited “the risk of antitrust penalties that could significantly impact Google’s U.S. distribution of search and search revenue.”

item.title: Neumora Therapeutics’ stock craters after trial of major depressive disorder fails to meet main goals
item.description: The news is a setback for the clinical-stage biotech and a drug that proved successful in earlier trials.

item.title: Gold Rises, Copper Flat as U.S. Dollar Rallies
item.description: Gold futures rose, beginning the new year on a positive note, as investors await fresh catalysts to decide the direction of precious metals.

item.title: U.S. Natural Gas Futures Start the Year With Gains
item.description: U.S. natural gas futures were higher, with the market looking to colder-than-usual temperatures for much of January to drive demand and reduce storage...

item.title: Dow Industrials Rise to Start New Year
item.description: The Dow Jones Industrial Average led major indexes higher, with chip stocks also rising.

item.title: Treasury Yields Get Support From Lower-Than-Forecast Jobless Claims
item.description: Treasury yields pared losses after weekly jobless claims data showed layoffs in the U.S. remained subdued.

item.title: Widen the aperture for space stocks to watch in 2025 — the story doesn’t begin and end with SpaceX and Boeing
item.description: After a big year for SpaceX — and one of misfortune for Boeing — here’s what to expect in the new year.

item.title: Dollar Hits 2-Year High on Prospect of Cautious Fed
item.description: The dollar’s momentum extended into 2025, amid expectations that the U.S. Federal Reserve will cut interest rates by less than other central banks.

item.title: Oil prices rise to kick off 2025, boosted by a stronger demand outlook
item.description: Oil futures began 2025 on a positive note, boosted by expectations for stronger demand.

item.title: Tesla’s first-ever drop in sales is a bearish sign for 2025. Will autonomous vehicles be enough?
item.description: Tesla’s “golden goose” will be a robotaxi, one analyst says.
